sequenceDiagram
  autonumber
  Client      ->> ShinyServer: request Shiny map app with a cell-values layer
  ShinyServer ->> DuckDB:      cell_stats(sql) for legend min/max
  DuckDB      ->> ShinyServer: min, max, mean, percentiles
  ShinyServer ->> Client:      return JS with tile URL template (base64 SQL, colormap, rescale, mtime)
  loop for every tile in the current viewport (z, x, y)
    Client      ->> Varnish:      request msens tile for z, x, y with sql, colormap, rescale
    alt cache hit
      Varnish   ->> Client:       return cached PNG (sub-ms)
    else cache miss
      Varnish   ->> TiTiler:      pass request through
      Note over TiTiler: validate SQL via sqlglot.<br/>LRU-cache cell_id-to-value map per SQL
      TiTiler   ->> DuckDB:        execute SELECT cell_id, value FROM ...
      DuckDB    ->> TiTiler:       rows (once per unique SQL, then LRU-cached)
      TiTiler   ->> CellIdCOG:     read z/x/y window (nearest-neighbor) from r_cellid.tif
      CellIdCOG ->> TiTiler:       256 by 256 uint32 cell-id tile
      Note over TiTiler: look up value per cell_id,<br/>rescale and colorize, render PNG
      TiTiler   ->> Varnish:       PNG (cached 7 days)
      Varnish   ->> Client:        return PNG
    end
  end
